**Memo:** Update from the Trail
**From:** Beth Hansen, Campaign Manager
Governor John Kasich had a very strong debate performance in Detroit last week and will travel to Miami on Thursday to participate in the next debate. Our focus this week is on finishing strong in Michigan and then shifting to Ohio and Illinois for the March 15th primaries. We had some exciting endorsements over the weekend and will need your ongoing support for our get-out-the-vote programs. Thank you for all that you're doing to help!

**The Detroit GOP Debate:**

Governor Kasich was the runaway winner in the Detroit debate, and it wasn't even close. With the field shrinking, primary and caucus voters had their first real chance to learn about John Kasich's results-oriented vision for America - and his performance was worth the wait.

Gov. Kasich's positive message and focus on his record broke through on a stage full of big talkers and hot rhetoric. Governor Kasich stood out because he is the only who has a positive record he can talk about and proven ability to get things done.

[](http://email.sermodigital.com/ct/34017960:WcmhV-CNW:m:1:958431888:9208BF00D0567B537E9214A90AA0202F:r)

**Major Endorsements:**

Former California Gov. Arnold Schwarzenegger joined Gov. Kasich for a weekend rally in Columbus, OH and announced his endorsement of John Kasich for President. Watch a short recap video here:

[](http://email.sermodigital.com/ct/34017961:WcmhV-CNW:m:1:958431888:9208BF00D0567B537E9214A90AA0202F:r)
Gov. Kasich received the endorsement of Michael Reagan over the weekend. [Read more here](http://email.sermodigital.com/ct/34017962:WcmhV-CNW:m:1:958431888:9208BF00D0567B537E9214A90AA0202F:r).
**
CPAC Remarks:**
Gov. John Kasich spoke at the CPAC conference and highlighted his record of getting results, balancing budgets and creating jobs. He received a standing ovation and participated in a Q&A with Sean Hannity afterward.

[](http://email.sermodigital.com/ct/34017963:WcmhV-CNW:m:1:958431888:9208BF00D0567B537E9214A90AA0202F:r)

**Volunteer!**
The Michigan Primary is on Tuesday the 8th and the Ohio primary is on March 15th. Will you commit to spend one or more hours helping with our Get-Out-The-Vote efforts? Sign up at: [JohnKasich.com/Volunteer](http://email.sermodigital.com/ct/34017964:WcmhV-CNW:m:1:958431888:9208BF00D0567B537E9214A90AA0202F:r)

**Upcoming Travel:**
Gov. Kasich was in Michigan today and will be again tomorrow morning for several campaign rallies with supporters before heading back to Ohio Tuesday evening for a rally in Cleveland. On Wednesday, he'll travel to Chicago to participate in two Town Hall events and a fundraiser and then fly down to Florida to participate in Thursday evening's CNN GOP Presidential Debate. He will return to Ohio on Friday to campaign in the Buckeye State through the March 15th Primary. If you'd like to attend an event, please find a list at: [JohnKasich.com/Events](http://email.sermodigital.com/ct/34017965:WcmhV-CNW:m:1:958431888:9208BF00D0567B537E9214A90AA0202F:r)

